  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Mechanism | Add Conjugate Cam FB</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading2">Add Conjugate Cam FB</para>
    <para styleclass="SeeAlso">See <link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Conjugate-Cam-FB">Conjugate-Cam dialog-box</link></para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_" style="text-indent:-36px; margin-left:36px;"><image src="tog_plus.gif" scale="100.00%" figurelistinclude="0"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="tog_plus.gif" src-expanded="tog_minus.gif"><caption><![CDATA[Two Cam Designs]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Table">In a cam-system, there are two design options to make sure that the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> (usually a Rolling Bearing) remains in continuous contact with the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profile</text> at all machine-speeds. </para>
          <list id="0" type="ol" listtype="upper-alpha" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="VariableName">Force-Closed</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> : an </text><text styleclass="VariableName">external force</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> pushes or pulls one </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> against one </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profile</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">. E.g. a Spring, Air-Cylinder, Gravity, Magnet, ...</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"><text styleclass="VariableName">Body-Closed</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> (also called </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Conjugate</text><text styleclass="Body Text">)</text> : two(2)* <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower, </text>interact with two <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profiles</text>. The <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profiles</text> are fixed to one machine-part (<text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Part</text>) and the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> are fixed to another machine-element (<text styleclass="VariableName">Follower-Part</text>). </li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">One of the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profiles</text> acts against one of the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Followers</text> to accelerate the <text styleclass="VariableName">Follower-Part</text>, and other <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profile</text> acts against the other <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> to decelerate the <text styleclass="VariableName">Follower-Part</text>. Together, it is impossible to move the <text styleclass="VariableName">Follower-Part</text> without moving the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Part.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">* There are exceptions to two </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Followers</text></para>
          <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#66;&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#41;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Noto Sans&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets"></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets">&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Groove-Cam</text><text styleclass="Body Text"> (also called </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Track-Cam</text><text styleclass="Body Text">) </text><text styleclass="VariableName">:</text> one <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> is &apos;trapped&apos; in a groove. The inner and outer face of the groove are the two <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profiles</text>, (sometimes called <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Flanks</text>). The <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> rolls along one <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Flank</text> as the <text styleclass="VariableName">Follower-Part</text> accelerates. The <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> roller switches <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Flanks</text> while the <text styleclass="VariableName">Follower-Part</text> decelerates. </li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Notes">Note:</text> The <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> must reverse its rolling direction when it switches <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Flanks</text>. The Cam-Follower must skid as it accelerates to its rolling speed</para>
          <list id="1" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#66;&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#41;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Noto Sans&apos;; font-size:11pt; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">&#32;<text styleclass="VariableName">Indexing-Cams</text> - there are often three, or even four <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Followers</text> in contact with the rotating <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Profile</text>.</li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Notes">Note:</para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><text styleclass="VariableName">Body-Closed Cams</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets"> are also called </text><text styleclass="VariableName">Conjugate-Cams</text><text styleclass="Body Text Howindent4bullets">. </text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">Why do we need a Conjugate-Cam FB in with a Conjugate Cam System?</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Interface2">Without a </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Conjugate Cam FB: </text>you can design <text styleclass="VariableName">Conjugate Cams</text>, and analyse their <text styleclass="Parameter">Pressure-Angle</text>, <text styleclass="Parameter">Radius-of-Curvature</text>, <text styleclass="Parameter">Sliding-Velocity</text>, and also calculate their <text styleclass="Parameter">Cam-Coordinates.</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text"><text styleclass="Interface2">With a </text><text styleclass="Element-Header">Conjugate Cam FB: </text>you can also calculate the <text styleclass="Parameter">Contact-Force</text>, <text styleclass="Parameter">Contact-Stress</text>, the <text styleclass="Parameter">Roller-Life</text> and <text styleclass="Parameter">Cam-Life</text> of each Cam. You must also <text styleclass="VariableName-indent">Configure the Power-Source</text> correctly, of course.</para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading4 Toggle_atocs_">2D-Cam: Elements, Parameters, Analysis, Coordinates</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1" style="border-width:0px; border-spacing:0px; border-collapse:collapse; cell-border-width:1px; border-color:#993300; border-style:solid; background-color:#ebebeb;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <list id="2" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Add a <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> - &#160;</text><text styleclass="SeeAlso">see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-Add2DCam" styleclass="SeeAlso">Add 2D-Cam</link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo">IF the new <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam</text> is will be a <text styleclass="VariableName">Conjugate-Cam </text> (<text styleclass="Element">Body-Closed Cam</text>) then</para>
          <list id="3" type="ol" listtype="lower-alpha" formatstring="&#32;&#49;&#46;&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;&#32;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="HowTo Bulleted" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Add <text styleclass="Element-Header">Conjugate-Cam FB</text> - <text styleclass="SeeAlso">see below</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Body Text">Edit the <text styleclass="Element">Conjugate-Cam FB</text> to add at least two <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cams</text> - <text styleclass="SeeAlso">see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-Conjugate-Cam-FB" styleclass="SeeAlso">Conjugate-Cam dialog-box</link>. </li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Normal"><line style="height:1px; color:#993300;" /></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Then:</para>
          <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="Body Text" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Text">Select the <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam</text> (or <text styleclass="Element">Conjugate-Cam FB</text>) &#160;as the <text styleclass="VariableName">Power Source</text> for the <text styleclass="VariableName">Cam-Follower</text> - <text styleclass="SeeAlso">see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-ConfigurePowerSource" styleclass="SeeAlso">Configure-Power Source</link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Then</para>
          <list id="4" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="2" styleclass="Body Text" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Body Text">Review the <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam&apos;s</text> Display, Properties, Cam-Life, and Roller-Life ...<text styleclass="SeeAlso"> - see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-2DCam" styleclass="SeeAlso">2D-Cam dialog-box</link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Then:</para>
          <list id="5" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="4" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Add a <text styleclass="Element">Cam-Data FB</text> - <text styleclass="SeeAlso">see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-FB-Cam-Data" styleclass="SeeAlso">Add Cam-Data FB</link><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">Select a </text><text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam </text><text styleclass="Body Text HowTo">to link it to the </text><text styleclass="Element">Cam-Data FB</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> - </text><text styleclass="SeeAlso">see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Command-FB-Cam-Data" anchor="CAMDATAFB-LINKTO2DCAM" styleclass="SeeAlso">Link the Cam-Data FB to a 2D-Cam</link></li>
          </list>
          <para styleclass="Body Text">Then:</para>
          <list id="6" type="ol" listtype="decimal" formatstring="&#37;&#48;&#58;&#115;&#46;" format-charset="DEFAULT_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="6" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:&apos;Segoe UI Semibold&apos;; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;">
            <li styleclass="Bullets">Analyze 5 different parameters for the <text styleclass="Element">2D-Cam</text><text styleclass="VariableName"> - </text><text styleclass="SeeAlso">see below</text><text styleclass="VariableName">&#32;</text></li>
            <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Body Text">Calculate the Cam-Coordinates</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> - </text><text styleclass="SeeAlso">see </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-Dialog-FunctionBlock-CamCoordinates" styleclass="SeeAlso">Cam-Coordinates dialog</link><text styleclass="Body Text">&#32;</text></li>
          </list>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading3_atocs_">Preparation</para>
    <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Standard" rowcount="1" colcount="2" style="width:auto;">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td style="width:200px;">
          <para styleclass="Normal"><image src="MD-FB-ADDCONJUGATECAM-01.ipp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Image Caption" figurelistinclude="0"></image></para>
        </td>
        <td>
          <para styleclass="VariableName">Preparation: <text styleclass="Body Text">The elements in the model before we do </text><text styleclass="T_Menu">Add 3D-Cam</text><text styleclass="Body Text">:</text></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Text HowTo"><table styleclass="Block" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
            <tr style="vertical-align:top">
              <td>
                <para styleclass="Bullets">Two(2)<text styleclass="HowTo Numbered">&#32;</text><text styleclass="Element">2D-Cams</text><text styleclass="Body Text" style="font-weight:bold;">&#32;</text></para>
                <list id="7" type="ul" listtype="bullet" formatstring="&#183;" format-charset="SYMBOL_CHARSET" levelreset="true" legalstyle="false" startfrom="1" styleclass="Bullets" style="font-family:Symbol; font-size:10pt; color:#000000;">
                  <li styleclass="Bullets"><text styleclass="Element">2D-Cams</text><text styleclass="HowTo Bulleted"> should be on one </text><text styleclass="Element">Part</text>. <text styleclass="Body Text">E.g. a </text><text styleclass="Interface">Crank</text></li>
                  <li styleclass="HowTo Bulleted">Follower-Rollers* should be on a different <text styleclass="Element">Part</text><text styleclass="Body Text">. E.g. a </text><text styleclass="Interface">Rocker</text></li>
                </list>
                <para styleclass="Body Table">* Rollers and/or Flat-Faced Followers.</para>
              </td>
            </tr>
          </table></para>
          <para styleclass="Body Table"><text styleclass="SeeAlso">See also </text><link displaytype="text" defaultstyle="true" type="topiclink" href="MD-POP-Cam-Follower-Shape" styleclass="SeeAlso">Shape of the Cam-Follower</link><text styleclass="SeeAlso">.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
